  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user I want application to be translated after I change the main device language.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Translations do not update immediately after language - only after app restart.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nApplication is translated immediately, just like other apps on the same device.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nApplication is still in the previous language. If I force stop the app and start it again, the language will be updated.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Open app\r\n2. Open menu\r\n3. Choose Settings > Languages & Inputs >  Languages\r\n4. Choose any language other than English and move it to the top of the list \r\n5. Open menu\r\n6. Switch back to status - see that the app is still in English\r\n7. Go to Settings again, then Applications.\r\n8. Find Status and Force stop it\r\n9. Open Status again - see that the language is now changed.\r\n\r\n\r\nTested on AVD emulator Pixel_XL_API_25(AVD) - 7.1.1",
